shared_text:
InspireNOLA Charter Schools
March 13 at 3:55 PM ·

Beginning Wednesday, March 18, InspireNOLA will provide meals to anyone 18 or below, from any school. InspireNOLA will set up two hubs to serve grab-and-go breakfast and lunches. Meals will be available Monday through Friday, from 9am to 12pm.

The hub locations are:

• Westbank – Alice Harte Charter School – 5300 Berkley Dr. New Orleans, LA 70131
• Eastbank – McDonogh #35 High School – 4000 Cadillac St. New Orleans, LA 70122

Please note: As other locations for meals become available across the city, we will post an updated list on our website and social media.

For more information visit, http://www.inspirenolacharterschools.org/coronavirus.

#InspireNOLA #NOLAEd

Free health screenings offered alongside backpacks at New Orleans back-to-school event

InspireNOLA Charter Schools
July 31, 2019 at 9:15 AM ·

It's more than just a backpack giveaway! Join us on Saturday to also receive free health care screenings (Eye, ear, and dental check-ups & Athletic Physicals) from Doc Griggs, learn about Cox's Connect2Compete program, Tutoring Services from CMP Educational Consulting Services, LLC, Parent resources from The Parenting Center at Children's Hospital and Families Helping Families NOLA, Library Services from Rosa F. Keller Library and Community Center, Mental Health services from the Broadmoor Improvement Association, After School programming from Community Works of Louisiana, and Free Haircuts from Stevenson Academy of Hair Design! #InspireNOLA
